# Design tokens & CSS

The rendered PDF's look is driven by three layered sources, in order of precedence:

1. `--accent` CLI flag (overrides only `--brand` / `--brand-soft`).
2. Parsed `DESIGN.md` tokens (emitted as `:root { ... }` + `[data-mode="dark"] { ... }` blocks by `buildDesignOverride` in [src/template.ts](src/template.ts)).
3. Bundled Claude baseline in [src/themes/tokens.css](src/themes/tokens.css).

## Hard invariants

- Never hardcode a color, font stack, or border-radius inside a component or rule outside `src/themes/`. Everything cascades from CSS custom properties declared in [src/themes/tokens.css](src/themes/tokens.css) and overridden at `:root` / `[data-mode="dark"]`.
- The single source of truth for palette slots is the `PaletteTokens` interface in [src/design.ts](src/design.ts). When you add a new slot, you MUST update, in this order:
  1. `PaletteTokens` in `src/design.ts` (add the TS field).
  2. The synonym rules in `SYNONYMS` (so `parseDesignMd` can detect the token in a DESIGN.md).
  3. `paletteToCss` map in [src/template.ts](src/template.ts) (TS field -> CSS custom property name).
  4. The default value for that CSS variable in [src/themes/tokens.css](src/themes/tokens.css).
  5. Any dark-mode override in [src/themes/tokens.css](src/themes/tokens.css) under `[data-mode="dark"]`.
  6. If the slot affects diagrams, extend `applyDesignToMermaid` in [src/mermaid-runtime.ts](src/mermaid-runtime.ts).
- Mermaid diagrams must follow the active palette. Do not fork a second theming pipeline; add new slot -> mermaid mappings inside `applyDesignToMermaid`.

## Dark mode

- Dark tokens are either parsed explicitly (a `## Dark palette` section in DESIGN.md) or synthesized via the inversion helpers in [src/design.ts](src/design.ts).
- Do not introduce a second dark-mode path. Extend `extractDarkPalette` instead.

## Font tokens

- `FontTokens` has only `serif`, `sans`, `mono`. If a design names a custom family that isn't installed, `appendFallback` in [src/template.ts](src/template.ts) adds a reliable cascade (Georgia / system-ui / JetBrains Mono). Do not remove the fallback; it's the reason the Claude baseline still renders correctly when a design references private fonts.

## Accent override

- `--accent <hex>` is intentionally a narrow shortcut: it only rewrites `--brand` and `--brand-soft`. Do not widen its scope. Users who want to retheme fully should pass `--design`.
